Michael Szabados - Chief Operating Officer










Facebook


Twitter


LinkedIn




Michael Szabados has served as NETSCOUT's Chief Operating Officer since April 2007. In this role, Mr. Szabados has focused on implementing and executing the company's vision and strategy. As COO, he has played a pivotal role in leading, integrating, and adapting the company’s functional areas as we grew dramatically through multiple acquisitions.
His career at NETSCOUT began in 1997 when he joined the company as Vice President of Marketing, charged with increasing our overall visibility and market awareness. His responsibilities expanded in 2001 to encompass product development, manufacturing, and customer support when he was promoted to Senior Vice President, Product Operations. A veteran of the enterprise networking industry, Mr. Szabados held senior leadership roles with companies including UB Networks, SynOptics/Bay Networks, and MIPS Corporation following engineering and product management roles at Intel Corporation and later at Apple.
Mr. Szabados holds a BSEE from UC Irvine and a Master of Business Administration from UC Santa Clara.





